-# Bulk-action bar. It sits in the index toolbar (next to the search box), but its
-# buttons submit the BulkForm that wraps the table — `form: "BulkForm"` ties them
-# to that form so the checked `ids[]` ride along. Hidden until JS (cafe_car.js)
-# reveals it once at least one row is selected.
.BulkActions{hidden: true, data: { bulk_bar: true }}
  - bulk_actions.each do |action|
    - danger = :danger if action.name == :destroy
    - label = t(action.name, default: action.label)
    - confirm = t(:bulk_confirm, scope: :helpers, default: "Apply “%{action}” to the selected rows?", action: label)
    = Button(*danger, tag: :button, type: :submit, form: "BulkForm", name: :bulk_action, value: action.name, data: { turbo_confirm: confirm }) do
      = label
